The paper deals with covert communication over wireless adhoc networks, which involves information theory (IT) and networking (NI) concepts. The paper also discusses the use of power control and preservation regions to achieve covert communication, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (CR). The paper proposes the use of multi-input multi-output (MIMO) transmission and scheduling, which falls under the category of multimedia (MM) and systems and control (SY).
